{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"22e32c03-ceeb-4abb-ba9a-43df862d5d97","content":"Your project isn't in the current directory, but here's how to configure it. Create `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"${workspaceFolder}/src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- Your server must use **stdio transport** (not HTTP/SSE). If using the `ModelContextProtocol` NuGet package, configure it with `.WithStdioServerTransport()`.\n- **Don't** write to stdout for logging — use stderr instead, or Copilot will fail to parse MCP messages.\n- After saving, open the Command Palette → **MCP: List Servers** to verify it's detected, then start a Copilot agent-mode chat to use your tools.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6c563d47-7906-4135-8634-52aa9fc98980","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project doesn't exist yet in the current directory, but the user says they built it. They're just asking for configuration guidance. Let me provide the answer directly.","outputTokens":312,"requestId":"7FCF:3C6787:478EB35:4E1C476:69F15B31"},"id":"096416ae-e5c8-48a7-8fc7-587273ddd66c","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:13:30.787Z","parentId":"7329de73-9faf-44d6-a6c5-d874905a7253"}
